<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1304" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1304">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.77/122.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                    Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Perhaps it would be worth while for you to make one more effort to induce
                            the American railway employees at least to postpone their walkout for a
                            few weeks, first, because so many of their countrymen would be affected
                            by deterioration of the service, and, second, because it seems quite
                            likely the opportunity to exclude Americans from future employment would
                            be welcomed by the Mexican Government. However, you will give no advice
                            inconsistent with the Department’s standing instructions to you of March
                            2, 2 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d1304fn1">See <ref target="#pg_731">p.
                                    731</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>